CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 26, 1958, pg. 3 reads: "Gifts for Gene Baker - Representing the youth of the community, this quartet visited Pirate baseball player, Gene Baker, in Presbyterian Hospital recently. They presented Gene with a Shakespeare fishing rod, which was donated by Sol's Stores in Wilkinsburg, and two Capitol record albums from Radio Station WEEP, where program director Bill Powell holds forth.  left to right: Patricia Prattis, John Touchstone, Carole VeLar and Eugene Sharpe. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Patricia Prattis (Jennings), John Touchstone, Carole VeLar, and Eugene Sharpe, presenting Pirate player Gene Baker with gifts in Presbyterian Hospital
